  <main>
    <!-- HERO -->
    <section class="page-hero">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="badge badge-warn badge-dot reveal" style="margin-bottom: 24px;">Where FRAZIYM began · v0.2.4</div>
        <h1 class="reveal reveal-delay-1" data-typewriter data-tw-delay="250" data-glitch style="margin-bottom: 20px;">XORZENX Framework</h1>
        <p class="reveal reveal-delay-2" style="color: var(--fg-muted); font-size: clamp(1rem, 1.3vw, 1.15rem); max-width: 620px; margin: 0 0 12px;">
          A next-generation deep learning framework engineered for <strong>Sparse Adaptive Intelligence</strong> — achieving the reasoning depth of multi-billion parameter models at a fraction of the computational cost.
        </p>
        <p class="reveal reveal-delay-2" style="color: var(--fg-dim); font-size: 0.9rem; max-width: 560px; margin: 0 0 32px;">
          XORZENX is the research project that founded FRAZIYM. Before AXONIX-ZERO, before the company — there was XORZENX.
        </p>
        <div class="btn-row reveal reveal-delay-3">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="contact.html#demo">Research inquiry</a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="https://github.com/Akik-Forazi/XORZENX" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ORIGIN STORY -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-label reveal">Foundation Story</div>
        <h2 class="reveal reveal-delay-1" style="margin-bottom: 16px;">FRAZIYM started here</h2>
        <p class="reveal reveal-delay-2" style="color: var(--fg-muted); max-width: 680px; margin-bottom: 48px;">
          Akik Faraji built XORZENX before building a company around it. The hypothesis was simple but radical: transformer models waste 90%+ of their compute on every single token. XORZENX was built to fix that — and the results validated the entire FRAZIYM thesis.
        </p>
        <div class="grid-3 reveal reveal-delay-2">
          <div class="card card-feature">
            <div class="badge badge-warn" style="margin-bottom: 12px;">The Problem</div>
            <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; margin-bottom: 8px;">Dense = Wasteful</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--fg-muted); font-size: 0.875rem; line-height: 1.6;">Standard transformers process every token through every layer with equal compute. A simple token like "the" gets the same compute as a complex reasoning token. This is the computational ceiling the industry is hitting.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card card-feature" style="border-color: rgba(77,240,200,0.2);">
            <div class="badge badge-accent" style="margin-bottom: 12px;">The Solution</div>
            <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; margin-bottom: 8px;">Sparse Adaptive Intelligence</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--fg-muted); font-size: 0.875rem; line-height: 1.6;">XORZENX routes each token through only the pathways, layers, and experts it actually needs. Complex tokens get deep processing. Simple tokens get fast-path execution. The model "thinks" proportionally to what's required.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card card-feature" style="border-color: rgba(107,123,255,0.2);">
            <div class="badge badge-cyan" style="margin-bottom: 12px;">The Result</div>
            <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; margin-bottom: 8px;">9.4% Active Parameters</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--fg-muted); font-size: 0.875rem; line-height: 1.6;">XORZENX-277M activates only ~26M parameters per token inference — yet matches the reasoning quality of dense 3B–7B models. This is the efficiency breakthrough that underpins the entire FRAZIYM product line.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ARCHITECTURE: HASS -->
    <section class="section" style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.01);">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-label reveal">Core Architecture</div>
        <h2 class="reveal reveal-delay-1">Hybrid Attention-Shard Switch (HASS)</h2>
        <p class="reveal reveal-delay-2" style="color: var(--fg-muted); max-width: 640px; margin-bottom: 48px;">
          The HASS block is XORZENX's core innovation. Unlike standard transformers that run fixed attention, HASS dynamically routes every token through one of three mathematically distinct pathways — choosing the cheapest path that preserves quality.
        </p>
        <div class="grid-3 reveal reveal-delay-2">
          <div class="card" style="border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);">
            <div style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.7rem; color: var(--accent); margin-bottom: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.08em;">PATHWAY 01</div>
            <h3 style="font-size: 0.95rem; margin-bottom: 8px;">Locality-Optimized Attention</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--fg-muted); font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6;">Windowed causal mechanism for high-precision local context processing. Used for tokens with strong local dependencies — code syntax, named entities, adjacent references.</p>
            <div style="margin-top: 12px; font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--fg-dim);">Best for: local context, syntax, entity resolution</div>
          </div>
          <div class="card" style="border-left: 3px solid var(--accent-2);">
            <div style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.7rem; color: var(--accent-2); margin-bottom: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.08em;">PATHWAY 02</div>
            <h3 style="font-size: 0.95rem; margin-bottom: 8px;">Low-Rank Global Manifold</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--fg-muted); font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6;">Compressed global attention that captures long-range dependencies without quadratic cost. Projects into a low-rank subspace — retaining semantics while drastically reducing compute.</p>
            <div style="margin-top: 12px; font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--fg-dim);">Best for: long-range dependencies, cross-document reasoning</div>
          </div>
          <div class="card" style="border-left: 3px solid var(--accent-3);">
            <div style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.7rem; color: var(--accent-3); margin-bottom: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.08em;">PATHWAY 03</div>
            <h3 style="font-size: 0.95rem; margin-bottom: 8px;">Temporal State Space Kernel (TSSK)</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--fg-muted); font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6;">Linear-time sequential processor using associative scan technology. Handles arbitrarily long sequences with constant memory — enabling virtually infinite context processing.</p>
            <div style="margin-top: 12px; font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--fg-dim);">Best for: infinite context, streaming, sequential patterns</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ADAPTIVE SPARSE ROUTING -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-label reveal">Intelligence Engine</div>
        <h2 class="reveal reveal-delay-1">Adaptive Sparse Routing (ASR)</h2>
        <p class="reveal reveal-delay-2" style="color: var(--fg-muted); max-width: 640px; margin-bottom: 48px;">
          The Adaptive Router makes three real-time decisions for every token — selecting the optimal pathway, depth, and compute width. This produces a model that is 90% sparse during inference.
        </p>
        <div class="grid-2 reveal reveal-delay-2">
          <div>
            <div class="terminal" style="margin-bottom: 24px;">
              <div class="terminal-bar"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span style="margin-left: auto; font-size: 0.7rem; opacity:0.4;">adaptive_router.py</span></div>
              <div class="terminal-body">
                <div class="t-dim"># Per-token routing decisions</div>
                <div><span class="t-blue">token</span> = <span class="t-ok">"calculate eigenvalues"</span></div>
                <br>
                <div class="t-dim"># Router evaluates cognitive load</div>
                <div><span class="t-prompt">→</span> pathway: <span class="t-ok">low_rank_global</span></div>
                <div><span class="t-prompt">→</span> active_depth: <span class="t-cmd">18 / 24 layers</span></div>
                <div><span class="t-prompt">→</span> width: <span class="t-cmd">1536 / 2048</span></div>
                <div><span class="t-prompt">→</span> experts: <span class="t-ok">expert_047, expert_112</span></div>
                <br>
                <div class="t-dim"># Result</div>
                <div><span class="t-ok">active_params: ~26M / 277M (9.4%)</span></div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 16px;">
            <div class="card card-feature">
              <h3 style="font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 6px;">Dynamic Depth</h3>
              <p style="color: var(--fg-muted); font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6;">Only activates the number of layers required. Simple tokens exit after 3–5 layers. Complex reasoning tokens may traverse all 24. Average: ~13 active layers per token.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card card-feature">
              <h3 style="font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 6px;">Variable Width</h3>
              <p style="color: var(--fg-muted); font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6;">Adjusts hidden dimension per token per layer from 384 up to 2048. 5 discrete width levels: 384, 768, 1152, 1536, 2048. Chosen based on token complexity score.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card card-feature">
              <h3 style="font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 6px;">Expert Selection</h3>
              <p style="color: var(--fg-muted); font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6;">From 192 available experts, top-2 are selected per token via dynamic gating. Load balancing ensures equitable expert utilization across training and inference.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- DISK-SHARDED MOE -->
    <section class="section" style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.01);">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-label reveal">Solving the Memory Wall</div>
        <h2 class="reveal reveal-delay-1">Disk-Sharded Mixture of Experts</h2>
        <p class="reveal reveal-delay-2" style="color: var(--fg-muted); max-width: 640px; margin-bottom: 40px;">
          Traditional MoE requires all expert weights in VRAM simultaneously. XORZENX solves this with a virtual memory approach — experts live on disk, a predictive LRU cache keeps hot experts in RAM, and pre-fetching eliminates latency.
        </p>
        <div class="grid-3 reveal reveal-delay-2">
          <div class="card card-feature">
            <div style="font-size: 1.8rem; margin-bottom: 10px;">192</div>
            <div style="font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--fg-dim); margin-bottom: 8px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em;">Specialized Experts</div>
            <p style="color: var(--fg-muted); font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.5;">Each expert is a specialized sub-network stored as an optimized binary shard. Trained to specialize in distinct domains: math, code, language, reasoning, factual recall.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card card-feature">
            <div style="font-size: 1.8rem; margin-bottom: 10px; color: var(--accent);">2 / token</div>
            <div style="font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--fg-dim); margin-bottom: 8px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em;">Active Experts</div>
            <p style="color: var(--fg-muted); font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.5;">Top-K gating selects only the 2 most relevant experts per token. The other 190 contribute zero compute. This is the mechanism behind the 277M model matching 10B dense performance.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card card-feature">
            <div style="font-size: 1.8rem; margin-bottom: 10px; color: var(--accent-2);">LRU Cache</div>
            <div style="font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--fg-dim); margin-bottom: 8px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em;">Predictive Pre-fetch</div>
            <p style="color: var(--fg-muted); font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.5;">Up to 24 expert shards cached in RAM at any time. The system predicts which experts the next token will need and pre-loads them — eliminating disk latency from the critical inference path.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- LATENT COT -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-label reveal">Reasoning System</div>
        <h2 class="reveal reveal-delay-1">Latent Chain-of-Thought (L-CoT)</h2>
        <p class="reveal reveal-delay-2" style="color: var(--fg-muted); max-width: 640px; margin-bottom: 48px;">
          XORZENX doesn't just predict the next token — it maintains an internal reasoning state across the entire forward pass. A 6-component vector evolves layer by layer, tracking the cognitive state of the inference process.
        </p>
        <div class="grid-3 reveal reveal-delay-2">
          <div class="card" style="border-top: 2px solid var(--accent);">
            <div style="font-family: var(--font-mono); color: var(--accent); font-size: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 8px;">COT[0]</div>
            <strong style="font-size: 0.9rem;">Intention</strong>
            <p style="color: var(--fg-muted); font-size: 0.82rem; margin-top: 6px; line-height: 1.5;">Goal-oriented state maintenance. Tracks what the current generation is trying to achieve across the entire sequence.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card" style="border-top: 2px solid var(--accent-2);">
            <div style="font-family: var(--font-mono); color: var(--accent-2); font-size: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 8px;">COT[1]</div>
            <strong style="font-size: 0.9rem;">Decomposition</strong>
            <p style="color: var(--fg-muted); font-size: 0.82rem; margin-top: 6px; line-height: 1.5;">Breaks complex tasks into sub-problems. Enables structured multi-step reasoning without explicit prompting.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card" style="border-top: 2px solid var(--accent-4);">
            <div style="font-family: var(--font-mono); color: var(--accent-4); font-size: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 8px;">COT[2]</div>
            <strong style="font-size: 0.9rem;">Confidence</strong>
            <p style="color: var(--fg-muted); font-size: 0.82rem; margin-top: 6px; line-height: 1.5;">Real-time uncertainty estimation per token. High-uncertainty tokens trigger deeper processing paths and more expert consultation.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card" style="border-top: 2px solid var(--accent-3);">
            <div style="font-family: var(--font-mono); color: var(--accent-3); font-size: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 8px;">COT[3]</div>
            <strong style="font-size: 0.9rem;">Contradiction</strong>
            <p style="color: var(--fg-muted); font-size: 0.82rem; margin-top: 6px; line-height: 1.5;">Internal error-checking and consistency validation. Detects when the current generation contradicts earlier context or stated goals.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card" style="border-top: 2px solid var(--accent);">
            <div style="font-family: var(--font-mono); color: var(--accent); font-size: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 8px;">COT[4]</div>
            <strong style="font-size: 0.9rem;">Direction</strong>
            <p style="color: var(--fg-muted); font-size: 0.82rem; margin-top: 6px; line-height: 1.5;">Logic-flow navigation — tracks which reasoning path is being followed and whether it's converging toward the goal state.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card" style="border-top: 2px solid var(--accent-2);">
            <div style="font-family: var(--font-mono); color: var(--accent-2); font-size: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 8px;">COT[5]</div>
            <strong style="font-size: 0.9rem;">Summary</strong>
            <p style="color: var(--fg-muted); font-size: 0.82rem; margin-top: 6px; line-height: 1.5;">Continuous state compression. Distills processed context into a dense representation so early information isn't forgotten over long sequences.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- MODEL FAMILY -->
    <section class="section" style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.01);">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-label reveal">Model Family</div>
        <h2 class="reveal reveal-delay-1">XORZENX Variants</h2>
        <p class="reveal reveal-delay-2" style="color: var(--fg-muted); max-width: 560px; margin-bottom: 40px;">
          Four model sizes covering every tier of the computing ecosystem — from microcontrollers to enterprise clusters.
        </p>
        <div class="tech-table reveal reveal-delay-2" style="overflow-x: auto;">
          <table>
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Variant</th>
                <th>Total Params</th>
                <th>Active / Token</th>
