              </tr>
              <tr style="background: rgba(77,240,200,0.04);">
                <td><strong style="color: var(--accent);">XORZENX-277M</strong> <span class="badge badge-accent" style="margin-left: 6px;">Flagship</span></td>
                <td>~280 Million</td>
                <td>~26 Million</td>
                <td>9.4%</td>
                <td>~50×</td>
                <td>Workstations, Servers, Coding AI</td>
                <td><span class="badge badge-accent">Architecture Ready</span></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>XORZENX-7B</strong></td>
                <td>~7 Billion</td>
                <td>~600 Million</td>
                <td>91.4%</td>
                <td>~100×</td>
                <td>Enterprise, AGI Research</td>
                <td><span class="badge badge-dim">Roadmap</span></td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CURRENT STATUS -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-label reveal">Verified Status · v0.2.4</div>
        <h2 class="reveal reveal-delay-1" style="margin-bottom: 40px;">What's production-ready today</h2>
        <div class="grid-2 reveal reveal-delay-2">
          <div>
            <div class="terminal" data-terminal-speed="fast">
              <div class="terminal-bar"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span style="margin-left: auto; font-size: 0.7rem; opacity:0.4;">test_all_fixes.py</span></div>
              <div class="terminal-body">
                <div class="t-dim"># XORZENX v0.2.4 — full system verification</div>
                <br>
                <div class="t-ok">✓ Model built successfully</div>
                <div class="t-dim">  Total params: 4,021,477 (XORZENX-1M)</div>
                <br>
                <div class="t-ok">✓ Forward pass OK</div>
                <div class="t-dim">  Output: torch.Size([2, 8, 4069])</div>
                <br>
                <div class="t-ok">✓ Backward pass OK</div>
                <div class="t-dim">  Loss: 9.6762 (scalar, stable)</div>
                <br>
                <div class="t-ok">✓ Gradient coverage: 327/327 (100.0%)</div>
                <div class="t-ok">✓ Deterministic inference verified</div>
                <div class="t-ok">✓ HASS pathways verified</div>
                <div class="t-ok">✓ Latent CoT integration verified</div>
                <div class="t-ok">✓ Tokenizer system functional</div>
                <br>
                <div class="t-ok">✓✓✓ ALL TESTS PASSED ✓✓✓</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 14px;">
            <div class="card card-feature">
              <div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; margin-bottom: 6px;">
                <strong style="font-size: 0.9rem;">Architecture Core</strong>
                <span class="badge badge-accent">100% ✓</span>
              </div>
              <p style="color: var(--fg-muted); font-size: 0.82rem;">HASS blocks, adaptive router, merger gate, CoT vector — all components verified with full gradient flow.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card card-feature">
              <div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; margin-bottom: 6px;">
                <strong style="font-size: 0.9rem;">Training System</strong>
                <span class="badge badge-accent">100% ✓</span>
              </div>
              <p style="color: var(--fg-muted); font-size: 0.82rem;">Trainer, checkpoint management, continuation, data pipeline, BPE tokenizer system — all functional and tested.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card card-feature">
              <div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; margin-bottom: 6px;">
                <strong style="font-size: 0.9rem;">Disk-Sharded MoE</strong>
                <span class="badge badge-accent">100% ✓</span>
              </div>
              <p style="color: var(--fg-muted); font-size: 0.82rem;">Expert fabric with LRU caching, predictive pre-fetch, and binary shard format — architecture complete. Expert specialization training in progress.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card card-feature">
              <div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; margin-bottom: 6px;">
                <strong style="font-size: 0.9rem;">Large-Scale Training</strong>
                <span class="badge badge-warn">Phase 2</span>
              </div>
              <p style="color: var(--fg-muted); font-size: 0.82rem;">Preparing WikiText / OpenWebText training runs for zero-277M. Architecture is validated; scale training is the next milestone.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- TOKENIZER & DATA -->
    <section class="section" style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.01);">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-label reveal">Data & Tokenization</div>
        <h2 class="reveal reveal-delay-1" style="margin-bottom: 40px;">Production-grade data system</h2>
        <div class="grid-3 reveal reveal-delay-2">
          <div class="card card-feature">
            <h3 style="font-size: 0.95rem; margin-bottom: 8px;">AGI-Ready Tokenizer</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--fg-muted); font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6;">Production BPE tokenizers in 5 vocabulary sizes: 1k, 4k, 10k, 16k, 32k. Includes 150+ special control tokens for multi-agent collaboration, tool-use, and structured output.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card card-feature">
            <h3 style="font-size: 0.95rem; margin-bottom: 8px;">Binary Stream Processing</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--fg-muted); font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6;">Zero-latency loading of terabyte-scale datasets via binary shard format. Supports JSONL, Parquet, HuggingFace, CSV, and raw text. Sharded dataset with streaming support.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card card-feature">
            <h3 style="font-size: 0.95rem; margin-bottom: 8px;">SPPQ Quantization</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--fg-muted); font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6;">Sharded Progressive Parameter Quantization — stabilizes weight training from fp32 → bf16 → int8 → int4 during training. Avoids the accuracy degradation typical of post-training quantization.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card card-feature">
            <h3 style="font-size: 0.95rem; margin-bottom: 8px;">Zero-Shot Transfer</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--fg-muted); font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6;">Inherits pre-trained weights from GPT-2 and LLaMA architectures with 100% gradient stability. Allows XORZENX to bootstrap from existing teacher models rather than training from random initialization.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card card-feature">
            <h3 style="font-size: 0.95rem; margin-bottom: 8px;">Adaptive Augmentation</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--fg-muted); font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6;">Data augmentation pipeline with configurable probability. Filtering for toxicity and low-quality samples. Shuffle buffer with deterministic seeding for reproducible training runs.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card card-feature">
            <h3 style="font-size: 0.95rem; margin-bottom: 8px;">Benchmark Suite</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--fg-muted); font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6;">Integrated benchmark runner with MNIST validation, accuracy tracking, loss curves, memory comparison, and Pareto frontier analysis. All metrics logged to CSV for reproducibility.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ROADMAP -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-label reveal">Build Phases</div>
        <h2 class="reveal reveal-delay-1" style="margin-bottom: 40px;">XORZENX development roadmap</h2>
        <div class="progress-tracker reveal reveal-delay-2">
          <div class="progress-step done">
            <div class="step-dot"></div>
            <div class="step-content">
              <strong>Phase 1 — Architecture & Bug Fixes</strong>
              <p>HASS block, adaptive router, L-CoT, disk-sharded MoE. All gradient flow issues resolved. 100% test coverage. Production-ready architecture.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="progress-step done">
            <div class="step-dot"></div>
            <div class="step-content">
              <strong>Phase 2 — Tokenizer & Data Pipeline</strong>
              <p>Production BPE tokenizers (1k–32k vocab). Binary dataset format. SPPQ quantization system. Zero-shot transfer from GPT/LLaMA teachers.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="progress-step active">
            <div class="step-dot"></div>
            <div class="step-content">
              <strong>Phase 3 — Large-Scale Training</strong>
              <p>Training zero-277M on WikiText-103 and OpenWebText. Expert specialization. Validation against dense baselines.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="progress-step pending">
            <div class="step-dot"></div>
            <div class="step-content">
              <strong>Phase 4 — xorzen0-inf C++ Runtime</strong>
              <p>Native C++ inference engine with SIMD sparse routing. Target: 10–50× speedup over standard PyTorch inference. Compiled binary distribution.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="progress-step pending">
            <div class="step-dot"></div>
            <div class="step-content">
              <strong>Phase 5 — MCP Tools Layer</strong>
              <p>Integrating XORZENX inference with file, browser, and terminal tool-use. Native MCP server support. Foundation for XORZENX-powered agents.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="progress-step pending">
            <div class="step-dot"></div>
            <div class="step-content">
              <strong>Phase 6 — Desktop App (Tauri)</strong>
              <p>React/Svelte chat UI. FastAPI inference server. Full offline desktop deployment. No cloud dependency.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="progress-step pending">
            <div class="step-dot"></div>
            <div class="step-content">
              <strong>Phase 7 — Distribution & XORZENX-V</strong>
              <p>HuggingFace model upload. Multimodal fusion, self-improving feedback loops, agentic recursive reasoning. XORZENX v0.3.0.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- IP & LICENSING -->
    <section class="section" style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.01);">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-label reveal">IP Strategy</div>
        <h2 class="reveal reveal-delay-1" style="margin-bottom: 32px;">Open weights. Closed runtime.</h2>
        <div class="grid-2 reveal reveal-delay-2">
          <div class="card card-feature" style="border-color: rgba(77,240,200,0.25);">
            <div class="badge badge-accent" style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Open Source</div>
            <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; margin-bottom: 8px;">Model Weights</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--fg-muted); font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6;">
              XORZENX model weights (zero-277M.safetensors) will be released on HuggingFace under a custom license. Researchers can validate claims, reproduce results, and fine-tune for non-commercial use. Transparency builds credibility.
            </p>
            <div style="margin-top: 16px; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--fg-dim);">zero-277M.safetensors → HuggingFace</div>
          </div>
          <div class="card card-feature" style="border-color: rgba(107,123,255,0.25);">
            <div class="badge badge-cyan" style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Closed Source</div>
            <h3 style="font-size: 1rem; margin-bottom: 8px;">xorzen0-inf Runtime</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--fg-muted); font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6;">
              The xorzen0-inf C++ inference engine is compiled binary only. The sparse routing logic, SIMD optimizations, and MoE caching are proprietary. Standard runtimes like llama.cpp run XORZENX weights dense — you need xorzen0-inf for the 50× speedup.
            </p>
            <div style="margin-top: 16px; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--fg-dim);">xorzen0-inf → Compiled binary distribution</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container" style="text-align: center; max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto;">
        <div class="badge badge-warn badge-dot reveal" style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Research inquiries open</div>
        <h2 class="reveal reveal-delay-1" style="margin-bottom: 16px;">Interested in XORZENX?</h2>
        <p class="reveal reveal-delay-2" style="color: var(--fg-muted); margin-bottom: 32px;">
          Whether you're a researcher, an enterprise evaluating efficient inference, or a hardware partner — reach out. Collaboration, licensing, and early access partnerships are considered case by case.
        </p>
        <div class="btn-row reveal reveal-delay-3" style="justify-content: center;">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="contact.html#demo">Contact Akik</a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="product.html">See full product →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
